<h4 id="star-generator"><em>Star Generator</em></h4>
<h5 id="visit-the-repo-1"><a href="https://github.com/phedayat/python-scripts/blob/master/turt.py">Visit the repo</a></h5>

<p>Built using Python with Turtle, I wrote a script that generates stars of <code class="language-plaintext highlighter-rouge">n</code> vertices repeatedly. Basically it draws stacked stars. The stars are drawn using simple geometric formulas for regular polygons. They direct what the turtle does for any <code class="language-plaintext highlighter-rouge">n</code>-sided polygon.</p>

<p>The script is easily runnable through a repl, and in fact the first mockup was made there.</p>
